Real estate investment trusts (REITs), such as National Storage Affiliates Trust and Realty Income, offer highly attractive dividend yields. Realty Income is one of the best REITs on the market, with close to 15,500 properties in eight countries, and has increased its dividend for 30 consecutive years.

Retailers, including Lowe's Companies and Target, are also Dividend Kings, with a history of increasing their dividend for at least 50 consecutive years. Target has increased its dividend for 52 consecutive years and has a strong digital channel and loyalty program.

Other dividend stocks to buy and hold in 2025 include Honda Motor, PepsiCo, United Parcel Service, and Verizon Communications, which have solid businesses built for the long term and pay juicy dividends.
